article.description: Sean Goldrich threw two touchdown passes and ran for another score, and New Hampshire held on to upset Colonial Athletic Association-leader Richmond 30-25 on Saturday night.
article.headline: New Hampshire beats CAA-leader Richmond 30-25
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Sean Goldrich threw two touchdown passes and ran for another score, and New Hampshire held on to upset Colonial Athletic Association-leader Richmond 30-25 on Saturday night. The Wildcats (5-4, 3-3) forced five turnovers, and snapped Richmond's (7-2, 5-1) seven-game winning streak. New Hampshire now has beaten the Spiders in five-straight games. Goldrich was 21-of-36 passing for 264 yards. Jordan Powell caught two touchdown passes (one from Adam Riese), and Kyon Taylor had a touchdown catch. Richmond's Kyle Lauletta was 19-of-38 passing for 240 yards with a touchdown, but threw four interceptions. The Wildcats led 27-15 before Gordon Collins ran for a 45-yard touchdown, and Peter Yoder kicked a 28-yard field goal to pull the Spiders to 27-25. Christian Breda's 29-yard field goal with six minutes left capped the scoring. The Spiders drove to the Wildcat 21-yard line before Lauletta threw an interception with five minutes remaining.
